[Gross (great) Glienike, a village located both in Berlin and Potsdam, the capital of the German state of Brandenburg, is situated nearly 100 km [62 mi] western to the German/Polish border. A map showing the location of Gross Glienike as well as the locations of infected wild boars sampled earlier in the affected territories in Germany and western Poland has been published in Twitter by Vincent ter Beek, editor of Pig Progress, and is available at https://twitter.com/vincenttb/status/1347497376886489088/photo/1.

If confirmed, this means a significant spread of ASF virus westward from eastern Brandenburg (444 cases) and northeast Saxony (17 cases), both stretched along the Polish border. Results of FLI's tests are anticipated soon. - Mod.AS

HealthMap/ProMED map:
Potsdam, Brandenburg, Germany: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=8085937,9404]
